.\" Man page for _printf - Holberton School
.TH _PRINTF 3 "November 27, 2025" "Holberton School" "C Library Functions"

.SH NAME
_printf \- custom formatted output function

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.BI "int _printf(const char *" format ", ...);"

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B _printf()
is a custom function that prints formatted output to the standard output
(stdout), similar to
.BR printf (3).
It takes a format string
.I format
as its first parameter and a variable list of arguments.

The
.I format
string may contain:
.IP \(bu 3
ordinary characters, printed exactly as they appear;
.IP \(bu 3
conversion specifiers introduced by the character '\%', replaced by the
text representation of the corresponding argument.

If
.I format
is
.BR NULL ,
.B _printf()
returns \-1 and does not print anything.

.PP
This implementation uses the library
.BR stdarg (3)
(\fB<stdarg.h>\fR) to read the variable argument list, and a structure of
function pointers to associate each conversion specifier with the
appropriate printing function.

.PP
The following conversion specifiers are supported:

.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.
The argument must be of type
.B int
(type promotion applies).

.TP
.B %s
Prints a null-terminated string.
The argument must be of type
.B char *.
If the string is
.BR NULL ,
nothing is printed for this specifier.

.TP
.B %d
Prints a signed decimal integer.
The argument must be of type
.B int.
Negative numbers are printed with a leading '\-'.

.TP
.B %i
Same as
.BR %d .
Prints a signed decimal integer.

.TP
.B %%
Prints a literal '\%' character.
No argument is consumed.

.PP
If an unknown character follows '\%', this implementation prints the
'\%' and the unknown specifier, then continues processing the rest
of the string.

.PP
This version of
.B _printf()
does not implement all features provided by the standard
.BR printf (3).
The following are
.B not supported:

.IP "Flags"
The flags
.BR '-' ,
.BR '+' ,
.BR ' ' ,
.BR '0'
and
.BR '#'
are not interpreted.

.IP "Field width"
No minimum width is supported.

.IP "Precision"
Precision is not implemented.

.IP "Length modifiers"
Length modifiers such as
.BR h ,
.BR l ,
.BR q ,
.BR L ,
.BR j ,
.BR z ,
.BR t ,
etc. are not supported.

.SH RETURN VALUE
On success,
.B _printf()
returns the total number of characters printed.
On error, it returns \-1.
An error occurs when
.I format
is
.BR NULL .

.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
#include "main.h"

int main(void)
{
	_printf("Let's try to printf a simple sentence.\\n");
	_printf("Character: %c\\n", 'H');
	_printf("String: %s\\n", "Holberton");
	_printf("Integer: %d and %i\\n", 420, -98);
	_printf("Negative: %d\\n", -762534);
	_printf("Percent sign: %%\\n");
    _printf("Unknown: %r\\n");
	return (0);
}
.fi

.PP
Program output:

.nf
Let's try to printf a simple sentence.
Character: H
String: Holberton
Integer: 420 and -98
Negative: -762534
Percent sign: %
Unknown : %r
.fi

.SH DATE
This manual page describes the version of
.B _printf
released on November 27, 2025.

